{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489351","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489351"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:14:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:14:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"640"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"640","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/640"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.07,0.31,0.06,0.42]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"640"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90305"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"640","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/640"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"640"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74559"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"492"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5643"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1995"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30968"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35354"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90305","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/90305"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman undergoes a repair of a massive incisional hernia and resection of an abdominal pannus, which had totally obscured her thighs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe has a medical history pulmonary embolism (occurred three weeks ago, treated with apixaban), obesity (BMI 35), and hypertension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe had been on intravenous unfractionated heparin infusion pre-operatively until shortly before surgery. Postoperatively, the surgical registrar made a decision to re-start the therapeutic intravenous unfractionated heparin infusion immediately after the six-hour operation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETwelve hours after her surgery, she had to be taken back to the operating room for evacuation of a large wound haematoma. The intensive care registrar was alerted to the administration of the therapeutic dose of the anticoagulant (not a prophylactic dose), with no documentation of any reasoning for doing so.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following would be the most appropriate action for the intensive care registrar to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Administer protamine sulfate for heparin reversal","Discuss the matter with a haematologist","Fill in an Incident Report","Report the incident to the Medical Board","Discuss the case with the surgical team"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAlthough this may appear like an error, there may have been some very good reasons why the patient was prescribed a therapeutic dose of heparin: she was at major risk of recurrence (recent pulmonary embolism, high BMI, and a high-risk procedure). The therapeutic heparin infusion may have been intentional and not a prescribing error. As always in such cases, a \u003Cstrong\u003Efull discussion\u003C/strong\u003E must first be held between all those concerned in the patient\u0027s immediate care before any other action is taken. Only once the discussion has occurred should treatment be decided on. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf the patient needed heparin reversal, then \u003Cstrong\u003Eprotamine sulfate\u003C/strong\u003E would be an appropriate option, but it has not yet been determined whether reversal is required. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf the surgical team and ICU team needed advice on treatment after their discussion, then \u003Cstrong\u003Econtacting a haematologist\u003C/strong\u003E would be appropriate. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReporting the incident, either via an incident report or to the medical board\u003C/strong\u003E, would be inappropriate as this is not necessarily an error. Any formal incident reporting should be left until a medical error can be clearly identified.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Effective documentation and communication between medical teams is essential to ensure patient care is optimised."],"references":["Spanakis SG. Disclosure after medical error. Curr Opin Anaesthesiol. 2021; 34:173-75."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74559"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"640"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74559","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/74559"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-13T17:06:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-04T20:28:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"640"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90305"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"e